16:31.535 --> 16:42.906
Coastal Management Act, which is modeled pretty 
much after the Federal Coastal Management Act of

16:31.535 --> 16:42.906
72. And they are now in the process of getting the 20 
coastal counties to organize a land use plan. This

16:48.751 --> 16:55.757
county, which ironically enough was the only 
county to support coastal management in 74, has

16:56.159 --> 17:24.259
now filed suit against the state declaring that 
the law is unconstitutional which means that in

16:56.159 --> 17:24.259
the meantime we're going to be without any sort of 
land use planning the county commissioners in

16:56.159 --> 17:24.259
yesterday's paper indicated that they intend to 
fill the void by starting a very thorough and

16:56.159 --> 17:24.259
exacting review of the existing ordinances in 
